<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
Privacy manifest for the Bristlenose Mac app (host shell only).

Required by Apple from 1 May 2024 for all App Store submissions. Declares
which "required reason" APIs the app uses and why.

Scope: this file covers the SwiftUI host (desktop/Bristlenose/Bristlenose/).
The bundled Python sidecar and every embedded framework (e.g. Python.framework)
need their own PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy at their respective bundle roots —
see docs/design-desktop-python-runtime.md when implementing.

Tracking: Bristlenose is local-first. The app does not track users across
apps or websites owned by other companies. NSPrivacyTracking = false.

Data collection: nothing is collected by Bristlenose itself. Interview
content and quotes stay on the user's machine. When the user configures an
LLM provider (Claude, ChatGPT, Azure OpenAI, Gemini), content is transmitted
to that provider under the user's own account — that is the provider's
data collection, not Bristlenose's, and is disclosed separately in the
in-app AI consent dialog (AIConsentView.swift, Apple Guideline 5.1.2(i)).

Required Reason APIs declared:
  - UserDefaults (NSUserDefaultsAccess)
      Reason: CA92.1 — "Access info from same app, per documentation."
      Triggered by: @AppStorage property wrappers throughout the app
      (selectedProjectID, aiConsentVersion, appearance settings, etc.).

  - File timestamp (NSFileTimestampAccess)
      Reason: C617.1 — "Display file timestamps to the person using the device."
      Triggered by: sidebar "last opened" display on project rows.

If you add a framework, SDK, or call that touches another required-reason
category (disk space, active keyboards, system boot time), add the
declaration below with a documented reason code. Apple's full list:
https://developer.apple.com/documentation/bundleresources/privacy_manifest_files/describing_use_of_required_reason_api
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>NSPrivacyTracking</key>
    <false/>
    <key>NSPrivacyTrackingDomains</key>
    <array/>
    <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes</key>
    <array/>
    <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes</key>
    <array>
        <dict>
            <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPIType</key>
            <string>NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryUserDefaults</string>
            <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypeReasons</key>
            <array>
                <string>CA92.1</string>
            </array>
        </dict>
        <dict>
            <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPIType</key>
            <string>NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryFileTimestamp</string>
            <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypeReasons</key>
            <array>
                <string>C617.1</string>
            </array>
        </dict>
    </array>
</dict>
</plist>
